Revision history for Eval-WithLexicals

1.003002 - 2014-12-23
  - fix test failures on perl 5.21.7 (RT#101086; thanks, Father Chrysostomos!)

1.003001 - 2014-08-16
  - include minimum perl version in metadata
  - hide some internal packages from getting indexed

1.003000 - 2014-06-13
  - Add documentation to tinyrepl script
  - Convert packaging to use Distar
  - Minor pod cleanups
  - Ensure hints testing works correctly, even under abnormal environment
    variables (RT#81479)
  - Correct hints test to run under perl 5.8 (RT#72766)
  - Also preserve active warnings when using HintPersistence plugin

1.2.0 2011-07-04 21:42:30
  - HintPersistence plugin to persist compile time hints (DGL)
  - Support plugins (DGL)
  - Make prelude configurable, so strictures can be optional (DGL)

1.1.0 2011-01-11 21:51:00
  - Add a #line directive so it's clearer where errors occurred (DGL)
  - Filter out lexicals called '&' since these are anon subs (MSTROUT)

1.0.0 2010-12-05 17:04:00
  - Initial release (MSTROUT)
